page.title: 16BIRDS AT CARVERS ROCKS
page.content:
At Carvers Rocks there are all kinds of different birds around. This means that it is very good for bird watching. There are water birds and the birds that just like flying about all the time, like{Yellow Hammers, {Chaffinches, Swallows, Blue tits}and {Great tits.}There are sign posts there to help you spot the different birds.
For the water birds there are {Mallards, Coots, Great Crested Grebes, {Tufted Ducks}and{Dabchicks.}We saw a {Tufted Duck}on the Nature Reserve part of the lake where the fishermen are not allowed to go, because it would frighten them. There was a{Great {Crested Grebe}on a nest. We did not go too close because we might frighten them, so we stayed on the other side. We must not take any eggs at all because it is against the law.
